detail_description: Dragon Bridge in Da Nang is a must-visit destination, offering a glamorous view of the city and showcasing four famous bridges: Thuan Phuoc Bridge, Han River Bridge, Dragon Bridge, and Tran Thi Ly Bridge. The 666-meter long bridge features a unique design with a mighty yellow dragon that breathes fire and water on weekends. Visitors can also enjoy special programs such as New Year's Eve art celebrations and traditional Vietnamese music performances at Dragon Bridge East Park.
name: Dragon Bridge
address: Đ. Nguyễn Văn Linh, Phước Ninh, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

excerpt: Compact museum displaying a collection of sculptures & cultural items like costumes & instruments.
detail_description: The Da Nang Museum of Cham Sculpture is a captivating destination for anyone interested in the rich cultural heritage of Vietnam. Established in 1915 and later expanded with a modern facility completed in 2011, this museum boasts an impressive collection that includes over 300 pieces of Cham artifacts, making it the largest of its kind globally.
name: Da Nang Museum of Cham Sculpture
address: Số 02 Đ. 2 Tháng 9, Phước Ninh, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

excerpt: Modern bridge that swings out of the way to allow ships to pass & that is lit up at night.
detail_description: Han River Bridge is a modern structure that can swing aside to make way for passing ships and is beautifully illuminated at night. It's one of the four main bridges in Da Nang and a popular attraction for visitors. Walking along this bridge offers a stunning view of the city, including other famous bridges like Thuan Phuoc Bridge, Dragon Bridge, and Tran Thi Ly Bridge.
name: Han River Bridge
address: Cầu Sông Hàn, An Hải Bắc, Sơn Trà, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Da Nang Cathedral, also known as the Chicken Church, is a charming pink-painted church with vibrant stained-glass windows and a striking bell tower topped by an iconic rooster weathervane. Constructed in 1923 by a French priest, it stands out amidst the surrounding buildings. Despite its modest interior, the cathedral's lovely design attracts friendly locals who are happy to accompany visitors exploring this historical site.
name: Da Nang Cathedral
address: 156 Trần Phú, Hải Châu 2, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

excerpt: Sprawling, buzzing market with thousands of vendors for produce, street food, clothing & housewares.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Da Nang, Con Market is a vibrant and historic marketplace that has been captivating visitors since 1940. This sprawling hub spans an impressive 14,000 square meters and features thousands of vendors offering everything from fresh produce to unique clothing and household items.
name: Con Market
address: 90 Hùng Vương, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

excerpt: Buzzing, multi-level indoor market with vendors selling food, clothing, fabrics & housewares.
detail_description: Han Market is a bustling indoor market located in Da Nang, Vietnam. It has been a prominent landmark since the 1940s and is situated at the intersection of Tran Phu Street, Bach Dang Street, Hung Vuong Street, and Tran Hung Dao Street. The market features multiple levels with hundreds of stalls offering a wide range of products including local produce, handicrafts, clothing, fabrics, housewares, and accessories.
name: Han Market
address: 119 Trần Phú, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

excerpt: Colorful temple featuring characteristic craftsmanship & a large, golden sitting Buddha statue.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Da Nang, Chùa Pháp Lâm is a vibrant temple that beautifully showcases intricate craftsmanship and stunning architecture. This two-storey pagoda, located along Ong Ich Khiem Street, is surrounded by lush greenery and meticulously maintained gardens, creating an oasis of tranquility amidst the city's hustle and bustle. Visitors are often captivated by the serene atmosphere where locals engage in morning prayers alongside monks going about their daily routines. The courtyard features impressive statues, including a magnificent 1.
name: Chùa Pháp Lâm
address: 574 Ông Ích Khiêm, Phước Ninh, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Da Nang has rapidly emerged as a favored holiday hotspot, attracting both local and international tourists, alongside a growing expat community. This vibrant city boasts an impressive array of dining options, particularly along the scenic stretch from Dragon Bridge to Han River Bridge. While it's tempting to stick with familiar Western fare, Da Nang's culinary scene is rich with local specialties just waiting to be discovered. For those intrigued by history and culture, the Museum of Cham Sculpture is an absolute gem in Da Nang.
name: Da Nang
address: Hải Châu District, Da Nang, Vietnam

excerpt: 4-lane suspension bridge, the longest in Vietnam, with footpaths on each side to enjoy views.
detail_description: Thuan Phuoc Bridge is the longest suspension bridge in Vietnam, featuring four lanes and footpaths on each side for pedestrians to enjoy stunning views. Taking a leisurely stroll along this bridge offers a fantastic opportunity to take in the panoramic vistas of Da Nang city and admire its famous bridges, including Thuan Phuoc Bridge, Han River Bridge, Dragon Bridge, and Tran Thi Ly Bridge.
name: Thuan Phuoc Bridge
address: Cầu Thuận Phước, Nại Hiên Đông, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

excerpt: Amusement park with a massive Ferris wheel & other rides plus themed areas based on Asian countries.
detail_description: When exploring Da Nang, Vietnam, a visit to Asia Park is an experience that shouldn't be overlooked. This modern amusement park boasts a stunning Ferris wheel that offers breathtaking views of the city skyline, especially enchanting at night. While it may not be the largest theme park in Southeast Asia, its charm lies in its unique themed areas inspired by various Asian countries and thrilling rides. Visitors often find themselves pleasantly surprised by the fun atmosphere and friendly staff.
name: Danang Downtown (formerly Asia Park)
address: 26RG+F7, Đ. 2 Tháng 9, Hoà Cường Bắc, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

excerpt: Museum devoted to the life of Ho Chi Minh, from his early childhood to becoming a national hero.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant city of Da Nang, the Ho Chi Minh Museum is a captivating tribute to the life and legacy of Vietnam's revered leader. Established in 1976 and opened to the public a year later, this museum offers an immersive experience that spans from Ho Chi Minh's childhood to his rise as a national hero. Visitors can explore meticulously recreated environments like Uncle Ho’s stilt house, complete with lush gardens and serene fish ponds that reflect his humble beginnings.
name: Ho Chi Minh Museum
address: 26X9+F2G, Duy Tân, Hoà Cường Bắc, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Nguyễn Văn Trỗi Bridge, located in Hoa Cuong Bac Ward, Hai Chau District, is home to a stone stele at its western end. This stele serves as a memorial for Martyr Nguyen Van Du, the final revolutionary soldier who sacrificed his life during the campaign to liberate Da Nang on March 29, 1975. He was on duty to secure the bridgehead area when he made the ultimate sacrifice.
name: Nguyễn Văn Trỗi Bridge
address: Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Lớp vẽ Rùa Art Studio is a must-visit destination in Northern and Central Vietnam. Start your day with a cup of coffee at Hope Coffee, Tranquil Books & Coffee, or Kawa Coffee. Indulge in delicious desserts like Chimney Cake By Jinhouse. Explore the vibrant street food scene on a Hanoi street food tour and visit the National Vietnam Historic Museum.
name: Lớp vẽ Rùa Art Studio
address: 86 Lý Triện, Thanh Khê Đông, Thanh Khê, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

excerpt: Amusement park featuring rides, plus activities, food & architecture from various Asian countries.
detail_description: Sun Wheel is a prominent attraction in Da Nang, Vietnam, located within the Asia Park amusement park. Standing at 115 meters tall with 64 cabins, it offers a breathtaking panoramic view of the city and its surroundings. The wheel ranks among the top five highest rotations globally and is often photographed alongside many bridges. Visitors can also enjoy various rides, activities, and diverse Asian architectural elements within the park.
name: Sun Wheel
address: 1 Phan Đăng Lưu, Hoà Cường Bắc, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng, Vietnam

excerpt: Cool hub of street food vendors featured in a small venue decorated with paper lanterns.
detail_description: Son Tra Night Market is a vibrant hub of street food vendors set in a charming venue adorned with paper lanterns. Established in 2018, it's conveniently located near the famous Dragon Bridge, known for its captivating nightly light show. This market offers an array of local delicacies at affordable prices and also features popular handicrafts such as colorful lanterns, traditional Vietnamese hats, pottery, and clothing.
name: Son Tra Night Market
address: Mai Hắc Đế, An Hải Trung, Sơn Trà, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Sky36 is a trendy three-story rooftop bar located in the heart of Da Nang City Centre, at Novotel Danang Premier Han River. It's a popular spot for affluent travelers and local elites who want to enjoy a stylish night out. The bar features neon-lit fixtures, state-of-the-art audiovisual systems, an outdoor bar, elegant sofa beds, and private VIP lounges.
name: Sky36
address: 36 Bạch Đằng, Thạch Thang, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Phạm Văn Đồng Beach has served as the backdrop for numerous film productions, a testament to its stunning natural beauty.
name: Phạm Văn Đồng
address: Sơn Trà, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Cầu Trần Thị Lý, also known as Trần Thị Lý Bridge, is a captivating cable bridge in Da Nang, Vietnam. Originally built as a railway bridge by the French in 1950, it has become a popular attraction for visitors. The elegant pylon and deck of the bridge are illuminated with changing colors every night, creating a mesmerizing sight during evening hours. It's an ideal spot for capturing stunning photos, especially during sunset.
name: Cầu Trần Thị Lý
address: Trần Thị Lý, Hòa Cường, Đà Nẵng, 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Sky Pub in Da Nang is a vibrant spot to enjoy delicious drinks while taking in the city's nighttime views. The pub features a lively atmosphere with top-notch DJ performances and an extensive drink selection, including large nitrous balloons for some added fun. While it may be a bit pricier, the experience is worth it for tourists seeking an exciting night out. Visitors can savor great cocktails and shisha while enjoying the friendly service and neon-lit ambiance.
name: Sky Pub
address: 214 Bạch Đằng, Phước Ninh, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: The Da Nang Family Cooking Class offers a cozy and authentic experience in the home of a friendly local family. Participants have praised the warm atmosphere and delicious food, describing it as an unforgettable experience. The instructors provide clear instructions on cooking Vietnamese dishes and even share recipes for participants to recreate at home. This class comes highly recommended for those looking to learn about Vietnamese cuisine in a welcoming environment.
name: Da Nang Family Cooking Class
address: 374/36 Núi Thành, Hoà Cường Bắc, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 50217, Vietnam

detail_description: Thuận Phước is a must-visit tourist spot in Danang, especially for photography enthusiasts. It's designed to resemble the charming farms of Europe, offering a romantic and picturesque setting that serves as an ideal studio for capturing stunning photographs.
name: Thuận Phước
address: Nại Hiên Đông, Sơn Trà, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

excerpt: Museum to the history of Da Nang, displaying cultural & military artifacts in a modern space.
detail_description: Da Nang Museum is a modern space showcasing cultural and military artifacts, offering a comprehensive look at the history of the city. In addition to alluring beaches, the city boasts cultural and historical attractions such as the Danang Museum of Cham Sculpture, revolutionary base K20, and Marble Mountains. Visitors can also explore intangible cultural heritages like Bai choi folk singing, Tuong classical opera, Whale worshipping ritual, and Avalokitesvara Bodhisattva festival.
name: Đà Nẵng Museum
address: 31 Trần Phú, P, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Trần Thị Lý is a charming destination that offers visitors a delightful experience. The place is known for its beautiful landscapes, serene atmosphere, and rich cultural heritage. Visitors can explore the local traditions and customs, savor delicious traditional cuisine, and immerse themselves in the warm hospitality of the locals. Trần Thị Lý is also famous for its stunning natural beauty, including lush greenery, picturesque mountains, and tranquil rivers.
name: Trần Thị Lý
address: Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Nguyen Hien Dinh Tuong Theater is a venue that showcases Vietnamese Classical Drama (Tuong), a captivating blend of folk dance and musical performances. The theater offers an hour-long immersive experience, where artists don traditional costumes and makeup to bring Vietnamese cultural traditions to life through storytelling. This cultural gem provides an opportunity for visitors to witness live acts of traditional Vietnamese performance art, featuring beautiful costumes and talented actors.
name: Tuong Theater Nguyen Hien Dinh
address: 155 Phan Châu Trinh, Phước Ninh, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: When visiting Da Nang, make sure to seek out Bánh Xèo Bà Dưỡng, a local favorite located down a small alley off Hoang Dieu Street. This eatery is renowned for its authentic bánh xèo, crispy savory pancakes filled with pork skewers, shrimp spring rolls, and fresh herbs.
name: Bánh Xèo Bà Dưỡng
address: 280/23 Hoàng Diệu, Phước Ninh, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: The Hàn River, a stunning gem in Da Nang, serves as the backdrop for an array of vibrant events and breathtaking scenery. As part of the upcoming 8th Viet Nam - Japan Festival, visitors can look forward to electrifying performances from renowned rock bands like On the Radio Band and True Blood Band. The festival will also feature spectacular fireworks displays from international teams along the riverbank, creating a magical atmosphere that runs from June 2 to July 8.
name: Hàn River
address: Da Nang, Vietnam

excerpt: Sprawling amusement park featuring rides & games for children, plus gardens, cafes & a food court.
detail_description: Helio Center is a sprawling amusement park and entertainment complex located in the heart of Da Nang city. It offers a wide range of activities for both children and adults, including rides, games, gardens, cafes, and a food court. The Helio Kids area provides hands-on playtime for children under 12 years old, while the Helio Play zone offers motion games and thrilling activities suitable for all ages.
name: Helio Center Amusement Center
address: Tòa nhà Helio, 01 Đ. 2 Tháng 9, Hoà Cường Bắc, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng, Vietnam

excerpt: Fine arts museum displaying paintings, sculptures, ceramics & more in a modern space with a cafe.
detail_description: The Danang Fine Arts Museum is a modern space that houses an impressive collection of paintings, sculptures, ceramics, and more. It is the third largest art museum in Vietnam and features a three-story building with diverse exhibitions. The first floor showcases native modern and alternative art, while the second floor preserves oil paintings, sculptures, lacquered paintings, and war arts. The third floor offers an assorted collection of traditional, ancient, and applied arts.
name: Danang Fine Arts Museum
address: 78 Đ. Lê Duẩn, Thạch Thang, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Embark on a culinary adventure with the Da Nang Food Tour, an immersive experience that takes you through the vibrant streets of the city. Led by knowledgeable guides, this tour offers a chance to taste authentic Vietnamese dishes from popular eateries and street vendors. Riding on motorbikes, visitors get to explore bustling backstreets while sampling local delicacies and gaining insights into the country's rich food culture.
name: Da Nang Food Tour
address: 4 Trần Quốc Toản, Hải Châu 1, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: "My Quang Ba Mua" is a renowned restaurant in Da Nang that offers a wide variety of toppings for the iconic dish, Mi Quang. This signature dish features chewy rice noodles colored with turmeric and served in a shallow pool of flavorful broth. Toppings include river shrimp, boiled quail eggs, roast pork, and an assortment of fresh herbs and vegetables such as basil, lettuce, coriander, peanuts, and banana blossoms.
name: My Quang Ba Mua
address: 95A Đ. Nguyễn Tri Phương, Thạc Gián, Thanh Khê, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Nhà hàng Madame Lân is a highly regarded dining establishment located in the charming city of Da Nang, situated along the scenic Han River. It has earned a stellar reputation for its genuine Vietnamese cuisine, delivering an authentic local culinary experience. The restaurant's founders are deeply passionate about the nuances of Vietnamese cooking and have cultivated a welcoming ambiance that perfectly complements the delectable array of dishes available.
name: Nhà hàng Madame Lân
address: 04 Bạch Đằng, Thạch Thang, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Hue Ngon Restaurant is a humble spot located just 5 minutes away from Da Nang Cathedral, making it a convenient stop for delicious Vietnamese BBQ. The menu features a variety of options including barbecued octopus, pork, squid in stone, and cow tendon at affordable prices ranging from VND 30,000 to VND 60,000. The restaurant's simple furnishings and reasonable prices make it an attractive choice for authentic Vietnamese cuisine.
name: Hue Ngon Restaurant
address: 65 Trần Quốc Toản, Phước Ninh, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Bún Mắm Bà Đông is a traditional southern Vietnamese dish believed to have originated in Soc Trang Province, located in the Mekong Delta. In central Vietnam, it consists of vermicelli, pork or roasted pork, vegetables, unripe papaya, peanuts and anchovy fish sauce. This dark fish sauce noodle soup resembles grilled pork vermicelli but uses barbeque pork with skin and a distinctively strong-smelling dark fish sauce.
name: Bún Mắm Bà Đông
address: 145 Huỳnh Thúc Kháng, Phước Ninh, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: New Golden Pine Pub is a popular late-night hangout in Da Nang, attracting both locals and expats with its relaxed atmosphere, lively parties, and friendly staff. Situated along Bach Dang Street, this three-story bar features a dance floor, multiple pool tables, and an outdoor terrace offering views of the illuminated Dragon River Bridge. The pub offers various drink options at affordable prices and also runs promotions daily.
name: New Golden Pine Pub
address: 325 Đ. Trần Hưng Đạo, An Hải Bắc, Sơn Trà, Đà Nẵng 590000, Vietnam

detail_description: Perched atop the Brilliant Hotel in Da Nang City Centre, Brilliant Top Bar offers a relaxing atmosphere with modern decor and floor-to-ceiling windows that provide expansive views of Han River, Khe Beach, and the city. This rooftop bar can accommodate about 100 people and is a popular spot for tourists and expats looking for a quiet evening out. The menu features a blend of international and Vietnamese fusion cuisine, including delicious tapas and refreshing cocktails.
name: Brilliant Top Bar
address: 162 Bạch Đằng, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Bún chả cá 109, located on Nguyen Chi Thanh street in Danang, has been serving authentic fish cake noodle soup for over 40 years. Despite its simple decor with plastic stools and low tables, this restaurant is a favorite among locals for its delicious bowls of bún chả cá made with fish, shrimp, and crab cakes. Visitors highly recommend this spot for a tasty and authentic dining experience.
name: Bún chả cá 109
address: 109 Nguyễn Chí Thanh, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: OQ Lounge Pub is a popular spot for those looking to end their night out on a high note. The bar offers a unique atmosphere that makes patrons feel like they're partying among friends. Guests can enjoy watching the bartenders skillfully mix cocktails while sitting close to the DJ box. Despite some initial concerns about the lighting, visitors are drawn back by the good music and friendly staff.
name: OQ Club
address: 18-20 Bạch Đằng, Thạch Thang, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Festival Carousel is located in Da Nang, which was recently recognized as Asia's Leading Festival and Events Destination. This vibrant city boasts a mix of modern architecture and ancient charm, set against the stunning backdrop of the Truong Son mountains and golden beaches. The carousel at Asia Park Da Nang offers a nostalgic yet epic experience, with colorful horses and shimmering lights creating a magical atmosphere. Visitors can enjoy this enchanting ride for two minutes, creating beautiful memories against the backdrop of this stylish city.
name: Festival Carousel
address: Vietnam, Hải Châu, Unnamed Road

detail_description: Min Luxury Spa offers a range of traditional Vietnamese massage techniques, including body massages with lotion and candle massages. The spa's skilled and experienced staff provide top-notch services to help guests relax and rejuvenate. In addition to massages, the spa also offers full body scrubs and teeth whitening treatments in a tranquil environment adorned with natural tones and materials.
name: Min Luxury Spa
address: 02 Tô Hiến Thành, Phước Mỹ, Sơn Trà, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Memory Lounge is an upscale 5-star restaurant with a distinctive leaf-shaped design, situated on the iconic Han River in Danang. It offers stunning views of the city's famous bridges including Thuan Phuoc Bridge, Han River Bridge, Dragon Bridge and Tran Thi Ly Bridge. The restaurant can accommodate up to 350 people and features a restaurant area, bar counter, and three luxurious VIP rooms.
name: Memory Lounge
address: 7 Bạch Đằng, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 59000, Vietnam

detail_description: APEC Park, situated in the heart of Da Nang, Vietnam, is a serene and well-maintained destination popular among locals and tourists. The park features over 20 statues crafted from various materials such as bronze and steel, representing 21 different global economies. Visitors can stroll along outlined pathways shaded by trees while enjoying the peaceful ambiance away from the city's hustle and bustle.
name: APEC Park
address: Phước Ninh, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Cong Caphe is a fascinating coffee shop in Da Nang, Vietnam, conveniently situated near the traditional market. It's known for its unique Vietnamese drinks featuring coconut milk, such as Coconut milk with green rice, Coconut milk with coffee, and Coconut milk with cocoa. The staff wears distinctive green Vietnamese army uniforms and provides excellent service with warm hospitality. The interior is spacious and offers various seating options including short stools and sofas.
name: Cong Caphe
address: 23 Lý Tự Trọng, Thạch Thang, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 50003, Vietnam

detail_description: Located atop the New Orient Hotel, F29 Golden Beef & Sky Bar offers a luxurious and modern rooftop experience in Da Nang. The stylish interior seamlessly blends with wrap-around terraces, providing stunning 360-degree views of the city skyline and river. The menu features a fusion of modern Mediterranean cuisine with an Asian twist, accompanied by an extensive cocktail list and a selection of wines and spirits.
name: F29 Golden Beef & Sky Bar
address: 01-A1, Lô, Lê Văn Duyệt, Nại Hiên Đông, Sơn Trà, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: If you're looking for a rejuvenating experience in Da Nang, the Luxury Herbal Spa is a must-visit. This renowned wellness spot offers a wide range of treatments, from traditional Vietnamese head massages to Shiatsu and herbal massages. The spa's Asian-inspired interiors and calming music create a tranquil atmosphere where you can relax and revitalize your skin with aroma body massages.
name: Luxury Herbal Spa
address: 201 D. Đình Nghệ, An Hải Bắc, Sơn Trà, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Vé Bà Nà Hills is a must-visit destination in the livable city, offering an unforgettable experience. Visitors can enjoy an exhilarating chairlift ride to the top, savor a sumptuous buffet, and marvel at the breathtaking views from the Golden Hand Bridge. The 4D theatre ride promises an unforgettable thrill. In addition to these attractions, visitors can explore the surreal French village and experience the alpine coaster.
name: Vé Bà Nà Hills
address: 1428 K 142 Nguyễn Duy Hiệu, An Hải Đông, Sơn Trà, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: Charm Spa Grand Da Nang is a renowned 5-star luxury spa located in the heart of Da Nang. With over a decade of experience, it offers top-notch professional massage services in an elegantly designed space. The spa features various massage packages, including Swedish, Thai, and Japanese styles. Notable treatments like Bamboo massage and Foot reflexology are among their specialties. Visitors praise the friendly and skilled staff who provide excellent service.
name: Charm Spa Grand Da Nang
address: 36 Thái Phiên, Phước Ninh, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam

detail_description: The Children's Cultural House in Hoi An is a vibrant and youthful space that hosts festivals like the mid-autumn or children's festival. The design is fresh and stands out, offering a fun place for kids to play and learn. With spacious grounds, walking paths, and a lake, it's an ideal spot for extracurricular activities. It also provides open access to school facilities and sports areas for all types of students to enjoy.
name: Danang Children's Palace
address: 2a Phan Đăng Lưu, Hoà Cường Bắc, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng, Vietnam

detail_description: Bắc Mỹ An is one of the stunning beaches in Da Nang, Vietnam, along with Khe Beach, Non Nuoc Beach, and Thanh Binh Beach. Choosing to stay at a hotel or resort on any of these beaches offers an opportunity to indulge in the refreshing blue waters and enjoy a relaxing beach vacation.
name: Bắc Mỹ An
address: Ngũ Hành Sơn, Da Nang, Vietnam

name: Danang local food restaurant
address: 176 Trần Phú, Phước Ninh, Hải Châu, Đà Nẵng 50000, Vietnam

excerpt: Network of 5 marble mountains with multiple caves, elaborate temples & viewing outlooks.
detail_description: The Marble Mountains, located in Ngu Hanh Son near Da Nang, are a stunning network of five marble hills that offer a unique blend of natural beauty and rich history. Visitors can explore numerous caves and intricate temples while enjoying breathtaking views from various lookout points. The mountains present an accessible adventure; while climbing to the summit can be challenging, there’s also an elevator for those who prefer a more leisurely ascent.
name: The Marble Mountains
address: 81 Huyền Trân Công Chúa, Hoà Hải, Ngũ Hành Sơn, Đà Nẵng 550000, Vietnam
